<br>
France is also posting SAMs at their reprocessing plant. The high level materials there dwarf the inventories at any power plant.<br>
<br>
PO...<br>
France has acknowledged that they grossly overbuilt. As bestonnet pointed out, nuclear plants are best suited as baseload generators (about a third of demand). At 75%, the plants are operated as load-followers which is poor economically and technically.<br>
<br>
The Government has suggested that nuclear capacity drop off to at most 60%, thus pulling the plug on any growth.<br>
<br>
Thus nuclear power peaked at 38% of France's energy supply (3.9 quads of nuclear generation out of 10.3 quads energy consumption)<br>
<br>
There is no Western nation which is planning any expansion of nuclear capacity. All have either stopped or actively off-lining nuclear plants.<br>
<br>
It is important NOT to consider the pleas of government or industry proponents for the heroic measures resuscitation of a collapsed industry for an actual approved policy by that government. Read the pleas carefully. They are beggings for attention.<br>
<br>
yale<br>
<br>
